Skeleton takes the 5 limb objects . In the
fuse_limbs() function, we set up any constraints
among 2 different limbs. For example, both legs
cannot be up in a given pose, also, the leg
cannot stretch so much such that it can be
completely vertical and aligned to the torso.
Such constraints among the limbs are taken
care of here. The set skeleton pose function
divides the 30-dim vector and calls relevant
functions in the limb objects, passing only the
part of the vector that is relevant to that limb
objects to create the limb. Here we
also make joint objects to ensure
